description: Borrowed from Japanese 力車 (rikisha), an abbreviation of 人力車 (jinrikisha), from Middle Chinese 人力 (nyin lik, “human power”) +‎ 車 (t͡ʃʰæ, “cart”) (compare Mandarin 人力車／人力车 (rénlìchē)).

entries.meaning: A two-wheeled carriage pulled along by a person.

verbs.description: rickshaw (third-person singular simple present rickshaws, present participle rickshawing, simple past and past participle rickshawed)

entries.meaning: To move someone by means of a rickshaw.
